      <section class="trivia-section">
        <h2>Trivia</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Origin:</strong> The Beagle breed originated in England, where it was used for hunting small game.</li>
          <li><strong>Appearance:</strong> Beagles are typically tricolored, with a combination of black, white, and tan markings.</li>
          <li><strong>Temperament:</strong> Beagles are known for being friendly, curious, and energetic. They make great family pets.</li>
          <li><strong>Popularity:</strong> The Beagle is a popular breed, ranking as the 6th most popular breed in the United States according to the AKC.</li>
          <li><strong>Famous Beagles:</strong> Snoopy from the Peanuts comic strip is perhaps the most famous Beagle of all time.</li>
        </ol>
